===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The [[private]] part of an [[Arab]] [[household]], traditionally forbidden to [[male]] [[stranger]]s.{{defdate|1841}}
#* '''1841''' ''The Mirza'', Volume 3, {{w|James Justinian Morier}}, p.&nbsp;153
#*: "In the room next to her own, lived the '''harem''' of a merchant who had just arrived from Constantinople with merchandise. It consisted of his wife, children, and two female slaves, who being well off in their circumstances, enjoyed the comforts and conveniences of life, and eat and drank unsparingly every day."
# A group of someone's [[girlfriend]]s, [[wife|wives]] and/or [[concubine]]s in a [[polygamous]] household.
# A group of female animals (cows) herded and controlled by a male animal (bull) of that species for breeding purposes. Such behaviour is exhibited by [[bovid]]s including cattle and buffalo as well as [[moose]], [[elephant]]s, [[seal]]s, [[sea lion]]s, [[baboon]]s, and [[elephant seal]]s.{{defdate|2006}}
#* '''2006''' Maestripieri, Dario; Mayhew, Jessica; Carlson, Cindy L.; Hoffman, Christy L.; and Radtke, Jennifer M. "One-Male Harems and Female Social Dynamics in Guinea Baboons", published in '' Folia Primatol'' 2007; '''78''':56–68, [[doi:10.1159/000095686|doi 10.1159/000095686]]
# {{lb|en|slang}} Any significant number of women together as a group; a [[bevy]].
# {{lb|en|uncountable}} A [[genre]] of [[anime]] and [[manga]] in which a man is the [[love interest]] of three or more women.

